            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EA%20proud%2C%20resistant%20heart%20pays%20no%20attention%20to%20the%20Word%20of%20God.%20Israel%20was%20stubborn%2C%20self-willed%2C%20disobedient%2C%20and%20hardhearted.%20How%20often%20have%20we%20followed%20suit%20and%20lived%20in%20habits%20and%20patterns%20that%20were%20obviously%20contrary%20to%20the%20Word%20of%20God%3F%20However%2C%20a%20tender%20heart%20that%20receives%20the%20Word%20of%20God%20and%20submits%20to%20it%20is%20precious%20to%20the%20Lord.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%20encouraged%20His%20disciples%20to%20be%20those%20of%20a%20noble%20and%20good%20heart%2C%20who%20heard%20the%20Word%2C%20retained%20it%2C%20and%20by%20persevering%20would%20%22steadily%20produce%20a%20huge%20harvest%22%20(Luke%208%3A15).%20The%20more%20tender%20our%20hearts%20and%20the%20more%20attentive%20our%20ears%2C%20the%20more%20revelation%20God%20will%20give%20us%20(v.%2018).%20Jesus'%20own%20mother%20and%20brothers%20did%20not%20qualify%20as%20much%20as%20those%20who%20heard%20God's%20Word%20and%20put%20it%20into%20practice%20(v.%2021).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20you%20read%20something%20in%20God's%20Word%2C%20receive%20it%20with%20a%20tender%2C%20honest%20heart.%20Give%20it%20first%20place%2C%20apply%20it%2C%20and%20let%20it%20change%20you.%20As%20you%20do%2C%20you%20will%20cultivate%20the%20ground%20of%20your%20heart%20for%20a%20harvest-thirty%2C%20sixty%2C%20and%20a%20hundredfold!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
